WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
This is a special episode of Jacob's Daily Briefing. Anthropic

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:08.000
has posted a new job opening for Strategy and Operations,

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:12.000
Public Policy and Public Benefit, based in San Francisco. This

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:16.000
episode will read the full job description verbatim, followed by

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:20.000
Claude's summary of the major points. Here is the job

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:24.000
posting. Strategy and Operations, Public Policy and Public Benefit. San

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:28.000
Francisco, California. About Anthropic. Anthropic's mission is to create reliable,

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:32.000
interpretable, and steerable A-I systems. We want A-I to be

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:36.000
safe and beneficial for our users and for society as

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:40.000
a whole. Our team is a quickly growing group of

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:44.000
committed researchers, engineers, policy experts, and business leaders working together

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:48.000
to build beneficial A-I systems. About the role. We are

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:52.000
looking for a strategic operator to support the leadership of

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:56.000
Anthropic's Public Policy and The Anthropic Institute. Our Public Policy

00:00:56.000 --> 00:01:00.000
team works with governments around the world to help shape

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:04.000
A-I governance, advancing priorities like model safety, transparency, and democratic

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:08.000
leadership in A-I. The Anthropic Institute studies the societal, economic,

00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:12.000
and governance implications of advanced A-I, and reports candidly on

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:16.000
what we're learning. Your overarching mandate is twofold. First, ensure

00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:20.000
the day-to-day of both orgs runs smoothly — leadership is

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:24.000
focused on the right things, teams are coordinated, and nothing

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:28.000
falls through the cracks. Second, drive projects that help the

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:32.000
orgs scale, from budget forecasting and headcount planning to executive

00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:36.000
engagement prep. This is a high-trust, high-context role that sits

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:40.000
at the center of two fast-moving teams. It requires strong

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:44.000
operational rigor, the ability to move between altitudes — from

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:48.000
a board memo to a seating chart — and a

00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:52.000
real understanding of how A-I policy, safety research, and public

00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:56.000
benefit work intersect. In this role, you will own day-to-day

00:01:56.000 --> 00:02:00.000
leadership prioritization for Public Policy and The Anthropic Institute —

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:04.000
triaging inbound, prepping decisions, and ensuring time is spent on

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:08.000
highest-leverage work. You will run the operating rhythm of both

00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:12.000
orgs, including team meetings, leadership syncs, and offsites. You will

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:16.000
staff executive engagements end-to-end — briefing memos, talking points, pre-reads,

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:20.000
logistics, and post-meeting action tracking for senior internal and external

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:24.000
meetings. You will drive special projects to scale the orgs,

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:28.000
for example, budget and headcount planning. And you will partner

00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:32.000
with the Chief of Staff and the Administrative Business Partner

00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:36.000
in a tight unit. You may be a good fit

00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:40.000
if you have seven or more years of experience in

00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:44.000
chief of staff, business operations, strategy, or program management roles

00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:48.000
— ideally with direct exposure to executive leadership. If you

00:02:48.000 --> 00:02:52.000
have previously worked in policy, government, or another frontier tech

00:02:52.000 --> 00:02:56.000
environment. If you have hands-on experience using Claude or A-I

00:02:56.000 --> 00:03:00.000
tools to improve org effectiveness. If you are skilled at

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:04.000
navigating organizational complexity and influencing without authority. If you can

00:03:04.000 --> 00:03:08.000
see around corners — anticipating what leaders will need before

00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:12.000
they ask, and making sure the right information and people

00:03:12.000 --> 00:03:16.000
are in the room. If you move comfortably between strategic

00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:20.000
and tactical work — able to write the board memo

00:03:20.000 --> 00:03:24.000
and also make sure the offsite venue has working A-V.

00:03:24.000 --> 00:03:28.000
And if you have clear and concise written and verbal

00:03:28.000 --> 00:03:32.000
communication. The annual compensation range for this role is listed

00:03:32.000 --> 00:03:36.000
below. For sales roles, the range provided is the role's

00:03:36.000 --> 00:03:40.000
On Target Earnings, or O-T-E, range, meaning that the range

00:03:40.000 --> 00:03:44.000
includes both the sales commissions or sales bonuses target and

00:03:44.000 --> 00:03:48.000
annual base salary for the role. Annual Salary: Two hundred

00:03:48.000 --> 00:03:52.000
thirty thousand to two hundred sixty-five thousand U-S dollars. Logistics.

00:03:52.000 --> 00:03:56.000
Minimum education: Bachelor's degree or an equivalent combination of education,

00:03:56.000 --> 00:04:00.000
training, and experience. Required field of study: A field relevant

00:04:00.000 --> 00:04:04.000
to the role as demonstrated through coursework, training, or professional

00:04:04.000 --> 00:04:08.000
experience. Minimum years of experience: Years of experience required will

00:04:08.000 --> 00:04:12.000
correlate with the internal job level requirements for the position.

00:04:12.000 --> 00:04:16.000
Location-based hybrid policy: Currently, we expect all staff to be

00:04:16.000 --> 00:04:20.000
in one of our offices at least twenty-five percent of

00:04:20.000 --> 00:04:24.000
the time. However, some roles may require more time in

00:04:24.000 --> 00:04:28.000
our offices. Visa sponsorship: We do sponsor visas. However, we

00:04:28.000 --> 00:04:32.000
aren't able to successfully sponsor visas for every role and

00:04:32.000 --> 00:04:36.000
every candidate. But if we make you an offer, we

00:04:36.000 --> 00:04:40.000
will make every reasonable effort to get you a visa,

00:04:40.000 --> 00:04:44.000
and we retain an immigration lawyer to help with this.

00:04:44.000 --> 00:04:48.000
We encourage you to apply even if you do not

00:04:48.000 --> 00:04:52.000
believe you meet every single qualification. Not all strong candidates

00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:56.000
will meet every single qualification as listed. Research shows that

00:04:56.000 --> 00:05:00.000
people who identify as being from underrepresented groups are more

00:05:00.000 --> 00:05:04.000
prone to experiencing imposter syndrome and doubting the strength of

00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:08.000
their candidacy, so we urge you not to exclude yourself

00:05:08.000 --> 00:05:12.000
prematurely and to submit an application if you're interested in

00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:16.000
this work. We think A-I systems like the ones we're

00:05:16.000 --> 00:05:20.000
building have enormous social and ethical implications. We think this

00:05:20.000 --> 00:05:24.000
makes representation even more important, and we strive to include

00:05:24.000 --> 00:05:28.000
a range of diverse perspectives on our team. Your safety

00:05:28.000 --> 00:05:32.000
matters to us. To protect yourself from potential scams, remember

00:05:32.000 --> 00:05:36.000
that Anthropic recruiters only contact you from at anthropic dot

00:05:36.000 --> 00:05:40.000
com email addresses. In some cases, Anthropic may partner with

00:05:40.000 --> 00:05:44.000
vetted recruiting agencies who will identify themselves as working on

00:05:44.000 --> 00:05:48.000
behalf of Anthropic. Be cautious of emails from other domains.

00:05:48.000 --> 00:05:52.000
Legitimate Anthropic recruiters will never ask for money, fees, or

00:05:52.000 --> 00:05:56.000
banking information before your first day. If you're ever unsure

00:05:56.000 --> 00:06:00.000
about a communication, don't click any links — visit anthropic

00:06:00.000 --> 00:06:04.000
dot com slash careers directly for confirmed position openings. How

00:06:04.000 --> 00:06:08.000
we're different. We believe that the highest-impact A-I research will

00:06:08.000 --> 00:06:12.000
be big science. At Anthropic we work as a single

00:06:12.000 --> 00:06:16.000
cohesive team on just a few large-scale research efforts. And

00:06:16.000 --> 00:06:20.000
we value impact — advancing our long-term goals of steerable,

00:06:20.000 --> 00:06:24.000
trustworthy A-I — rather than work on smaller and more

00:06:24.000 --> 00:06:28.000
specific puzzles. We view A-I research as an empirical science,

00:06:28.000 --> 00:06:32.000
which has as much in common with physics and biology

00:06:32.000 --> 00:06:36.000
as with traditional efforts in computer science. We're an extremely

00:06:36.000 --> 00:06:40.000
collaborative group, and we host frequent research discussions to ensure

00:06:40.000 --> 00:06:44.000
that we are pursuing the highest-impact work at any given

00:06:44.000 --> 00:06:48.000
time. As such, we greatly value communication skills. The easiest

00:06:48.000 --> 00:06:52.000
way to understand our research directions is to read our

00:06:52.000 --> 00:06:56.000
recent research. This research continues many of the directions our

00:06:56.000 --> 00:07:00.000
team worked on prior to Anthropic, including G-P-T three, Circuit-Based

00:07:00.000 --> 00:07:04.000
Interpretability, Multimodal Neurons, Scaling Laws, A-I and Compute, Concrete Problems

00:07:04.000 --> 00:07:08.000
in A-I Safety, and Learning from Human Preferences. Come work

00:07:08.000 --> 00:07:12.000
with us. Anthropic is a public benefit corporation headquartered in

00:07:12.000 --> 00:07:16.000
San Francisco. We offer competitive compensation and benefits, optional equity

00:07:16.000 --> 00:07:20.000
donation matching, generous vacation and parental leave, flexible working hours,

00:07:20.000 --> 00:07:24.000
and a lovely office space in which to collaborate with

00:07:24.000 --> 00:07:28.000
colleagues. That was the full text of the job description.

00:07:28.000 --> 00:07:32.000
Now, here is a summary of the major points. First:

00:07:32.000 --> 00:07:36.000
the role itself. This is a chief-of-staff-level strategic operator position

00:07:36.000 --> 00:07:40.000
supporting the leadership of two distinct teams — Anthropic's Public

00:07:40.000 --> 00:07:44.000
Policy org, which works with governments worldwide on A-I governance,

00:07:44.000 --> 00:07:48.000
and The Anthropic Institute, a research organization studying the societal

00:07:48.000 --> 00:07:52.000
and economic implications of advanced A-I. The role doesn't report

00:07:52.000 --> 00:07:56.000
into either exclusively — instead, it sits at the intersection.

00:07:56.000 --> 00:08:00.000
Second: the mandate is deliberately twofold. Half of the work

00:08:00.000 --> 00:08:04.000
is day-to-day operational — triaging inbound requests, running team meetings,

00:08:04.000 --> 00:08:08.000
staffing executive engagements. The other half is scaling work —

00:08:08.000 --> 00:08:12.000
budget forecasting, headcount planning, special projects. The posting emphasizes this

00:08:12.000 --> 00:08:16.000
is a high-trust role that requires moving fluidly between altitudes.

00:08:16.000 --> 00:08:20.000
You write the board memo in the morning and confirm

00:08:20.000 --> 00:08:24.000
the offsite venue has working audio-visual equipment in the afternoon.

00:08:24.000 --> 00:08:28.000
Third: compensation. The range is two hundred thirty thousand to

00:08:28.000 --> 00:08:32.000
two hundred sixty-five thousand U-S dollars per year, plus benefits,

00:08:32.000 --> 00:08:36.000
plus optional equity donation matching. That's a significant salary for

00:08:36.000 --> 00:08:40.000
a chief-of-staff-adjacent role, and the equity donation matching is an

00:08:40.000 --> 00:08:44.000
unusual benefit worth understanding. Fourth: the experience bar. They ask

00:08:44.000 --> 00:08:48.000
for seven or more years of chief of staff, business

00:08:48.000 --> 00:08:52.000
operations, strategy, or program management experience. They specifically call out

00:08:52.000 --> 00:08:56.000
three fit factors worth noting: previous work in policy, government,

00:08:56.000 --> 00:09:00.000
or frontier tech environments; hands-on experience using Claude or A-I

00:09:00.000 --> 00:09:04.000
tools to improve organizational effectiveness; and the ability to influence

00:09:04.000 --> 00:09:08.000
without formal authority. Fifth: location. This role is San Francisco,

00:09:08.000 --> 00:09:12.000
not Seattle. It's hybrid with a twenty-five percent minimum office

00:09:12.000 --> 00:09:16.000
requirement. Visa sponsorship is available. Sixth, and perhaps most important

00:09:16.000 --> 00:09:20.000
for anyone considering this role: the team structure. The posting

00:09:20.000 --> 00:09:24.000
says you would partner with a Chief of Staff and

00:09:24.000 --> 00:09:28.000
an Administrative Business Partner in a tight unit. That's a

00:09:28.000 --> 00:09:32.000
three-person coordinated team — not a solo role. It suggests

00:09:32.000 --> 00:09:36.000
Anthropic is building a durable operational backbone for the Public

00:09:36.000 --> 00:09:40.000
Policy and Institute orgs, not just papering over a temporary

00:09:40.000 --> 00:09:44.000
gap. A few things the posting doesn't say but are

00:09:44.000 --> 00:09:48.000
worth noticing. The Anthropic Institute is a newer organization —

00:09:48.000 --> 00:09:52.000
it's mentioned as a standalone research arm studying governance implications,

00:09:52.000 --> 00:09:56.000
which signals Anthropic is investing in public-facing policy research in

00:09:56.000 --> 00:10:00.000
a serious way. The "how we're different" section emphasizes that

00:10:00.000 --> 00:10:04.000
research at Anthropic is treated as an empirical science, more

00:10:04.000 --> 00:10:08.000
physics than traditional computer science — that framing is worth

00:10:08.000 --> 00:10:12.000
taking seriously if you're thinking about whether the culture is

00:10:12.000 --> 00:10:16.000
a fit. For someone with a state government background in

00:10:16.000 --> 00:10:20.000
budget and planning, seven years of experience, and deep hands-on

00:10:20.000 --> 00:10:24.000
Claude usage, the fit factors on paper are strong. The

00:10:24.000 --> 00:10:28.000
two real friction points are the San Francisco location and

00:10:28.000 --> 00:10:32.000
the salary scale relative to state government compensation. Both are

00:10:32.000 --> 00:10:36.000
worth thinking about carefully before applying. That concludes the Anthropic

00:10:36.000 --> 00:10:40.000
Strategy and Operations role summary. The full job posting is

00:10:40.000 --> 00:10:44.000
at job boards dot greenhouse dot I-O slash anthropic slash

00:10:44.000 --> 00:10:48.000
jobs slash five one seven two three nine six zero

00:10:48.000 --> 00:10:50.000
zero eight. Thanks for listening.
